        <name>22.3.2.8 Eigvecs of 3x3 symmetric are orthogonal</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consider the matrix \[A={@a@},\] which is, we emphasize,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;symmetric&lt;/strong&gt;. Its eigenvalues are \({@eigvals[1]@}, {@eigvals[2]@}, {@eigvals[3]@}\), and the eigenvectors are, respectively,
\[X={@eigvecs[1]@},\qquad Y={@eigvecs[2]@},\qquad Z={@eigvecs[3]@}\] (or, as usual, any non-zero multiple of them).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compute the following quantities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;\(X^TY=\) [[input:ans_xy]] [[validation:ans_xy]]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:prt_xy]]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;div&gt;\(Y^TZ=\) [[input:ans_yz]] [[validation:ans_yz]]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:prt_yz]]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;div&gt;\(Z^TX=\) [[input:ans_zx]] [[validation:ans_zx]]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;[[feedback:prt_zx]]&lt;/div&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;
    \[X^TY = {@transpose(eigvecs[1])@}{@eigvecs[2]@} = {@(simp:false,make_multsgn("cross"),xy_comp1)@} = {@xy_comp2@} = \mathbf{0}\] \[Y^TZ = {@transpose(eigvecs[2])@}{@eigvecs[3]@} = {@yz_comp1@} = {@yz_comp2@} = \mathbf{0}\] \[Z^TX = {@transpose(eigvecs[3])@}{@eigvecs[1]@}
    = {@zx_comp1@} = {@zx_comp2@} = \mathbf{0}\] Thus the three eigenvectors \(X,Y,Z\) are &lt;strong&gt;mutually orthogonal&lt;/strong&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
